page.title: 01Spaunton Moor East
page.content: In the middle of the north York Moor National Park close to Rosedale Abbey Spaunton Moor is typicl of the aea rolling bbrren moorland intersected by Deep Valleys. At 251 mtrs in predominantly heather grazed by sweep giving way to rough grazing for cattle in the valleys. Scattered farms populate the valley floor. Isolated during the witer but popular with tourists during the summer. The area hs few amenities with main towns being Whitby 30km and Scrborough 52km away. The Eastern section of the area is a small section of the large cropton forest plantation
